            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost">A</supplied>ram pro salu<lb break="no" n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>em <note>sic</note> <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ubli</ex></expan> Pet<supplied reason="lost">ro</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">n</supplied>ii Caesii R<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ufi</supplied> <lb n="4"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>io C<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="5"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">Ap</supplied>ro e<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied> Ma<lb break="no" n="6"/><supplied reason="lost">xim</supplied>o <expan><abbr>cons</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>K</abbr><ex>alendis</ex></expan> <lb n="7"/><supplied reason="lost">De</supplied>cenbri<lb break="no" n="8"/>bus <note>sic</note>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In zwei Teile zerbrochen. Buchstabe E in Form von II geschrieben. Schillinger-Häfele gibt für den Namen des Mannes, für den dieser Altar errichtet worden ist, als zweite Möglichkeit P. Pet[ron]ii Caeser[nii] an. Autopsie R. Wiegels. Hauptbearbeiterin B. Esch.</p>
            </div>
